cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another likely sub-category as the paper focuses on the dynamics of gradient descent in neural networks. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible sub-category as the paper deals with the behavior of neural networks, which are a key component of many AI systems. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a possible sub-category as the paper mentions empirical observations about deep learning, which often involves computer vision tasks such as image classification. 

cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely sub-category, but still possible as the paper discusses a modification to gradient descent that can reduce overfitting, which is relevant to control systems.
